Western Cape premier Alan Winde says the health system is coping and there's no need for the national state of disaster anymore. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - It's time to lift the national state of disaster. At least that's what Western Cape premier Alan Winde believes. READ: COVID-19 | Curfew lifted He says the health system is coping and there's no need for it anymore. Winde welcomed the recent lifting of lockdown restrictions. WATCH: Discussion | Ceasing the State of Disaster "I am feeling more and more optimistic, we've been saying for the last couple of days that it feels like we're in the peak," Winde said. "In actual fact, I'm supportive of removing the whole disaster declaration, I don't think we need to be in a state of disaster now."